Rule.fixtext:
Develop and document a contingency plan for the Voice Video system that identifies communications priority for mission-critical decision-making users of the DISN Voice Precedence service.

The contingency plan must include considerations for:

- Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) sufficient to support requirements (eight hours for Flash/Flash Override; two hours for Immediate/Priority for DISN Voice Precedence);
- Network infrastructure redundancy to support Assured Services;
- Geographically diverse pathways for location WAN connections;
- Session manager on location and sustainable WAN connections; and
- Voice Video endpoints and session managers support AS-SIP.

check.check-content:
Review the contingency plan for the Voice Video system that identifies essential missions, specifically communications priority for mission-critical decision-making users of the DISN Voice Precedence service. The contingency plan must include considerations for DISN Voice Precedence service as follows:

- Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) sufficient to support requirements
(eight hours for Flash/Flash Override; two hours for Immediate/Priority for DISN Voice Precedence);
- Network infrastructure redundancy to support Assured Services;
- Geographically diverse pathways for location WAN connections;
- Session manager on location and sustainable WAN connections; and
- Voice Video endpoints and session managers support AS-SIP.

If the contingency plan for the Voice Video system that identifies communications priority for mission-critical decision-making users of the DISN Voice Precedence service does not fully support this service, this is a finding.

Rule.fixtext:
Develop and document a contingency plan for the Voice Video system that identifies FES communications. The contingency plan must include considerations for:

- Network infrastructure redundancy to support high availability;
- UPS sufficient to support infrastructure availability;
- Session manager on location with sustainable WAN connections or local commercial service;
- Voice video endpoints and session managers support ANI and PS-ALI; and
- User training, to include use of mobile devices, Voice Video system, or other means.

